<h1>System Detect</h1>
<p>Project repo: <a href='https://github.com/nathan242/system_detect'>LINK</a></p>

<h4>Introduction</h4>
<p>Hardware information utility for Windows written in Python.</p>
<p>This requires Python 2 with the <strong>wmi</strong> and <strong>pywin32</strong> modules.</p>
<img src='images/system_detect-main.png'>

<h4>Details</h4>
<p>This utility will show hardware specifications such as CPU model, RAM size, HDD model/size and will also show the Windows BIOS license key if one is present.</p>
<p>Hardware information is retrieved using WMI and the BIOS license key is obtained by calling <strong>GetSystemFirmwareTable()</strong> from kernel32.dll (using ctypes).</p>

